commit.message: Add support for Python 3.11

Update release checklist

(no need to git push twice in succession)

Also: twine uploads now use '--repository' args of colorama and
colorama-test, which need defining in .pypirc. Making project-specific
repo entries like this allows me to use a project-specific token
from pypi, rather than one that grants all privs to every project.

Also: bump version number of 0.4.7dev1
bump version 0.4.6
Format the CHANGELOG bullet list, no content change
comment need for a fix after recent MP broke it
fix test-release after recent MPs broke it
README tweaks
Bump version to 0.4.6rc1
'make bootstrap' uses system python3, not pinned v3.8
CHANGELOG updates for upcoming 0.4.6 release
Tweak ordering of release checklist
